      "content": "A closer examination of the Apex Phone Pro and Zenith X reveals a multitude of differences across various hardware aspects. The Apex Pro boasts a 6.7-inch OLED display with a higher 120Hz refresh rate, resulting in a smoother and more detailed visual experience, especially in fast-paced actions. In contrast, the Zenith X is confined to a 6.5-inch LCD with a moderate 60Hz refresh rate, lacking the Apex Pro's high refresh rate. This highlights a critical disparity between the two devices, with the Apex Pro marking a significant step forward in display technology.\n\nWhen it comes to camera capabilities, the Apex Pro takes the lead with its 50MP main camera paired with a 12MP ultrawide lens, providing users with greater flexibility and improved image quality. This is complemented by the Zenith X's 48MP main camera and 10MP ultrawide lens, offering most of the same features but at a smaller sensor size. Furthermore, the Apex Pro's advanced camera features, such as optical zoom and enhanced low-light capabilities, make its camera more suited for demanding photographers and videographers. \n\nOn the performance front, the Zenith X is powered by the mid-range Dimensity 9300 chip,",
